# CONSULT-38 (DETAIL): D3D9 dot3/hemispheric seeding for empty-list precalc draws

## Executive answer

**`setFullAmbientOn(true)` does not seed dot3 direction or hemispheric constants in D3D9.** It only sets `ms_fullAmbient` to `(1,1,1,0)` (`Direct3d9_LightManager.h:201-208`), which flows into `lightData.ambient` (VS **c16**) via `selectLights` (`Direct3d9_LightManager.cpp:404`) and `applyLights_vertexShader` (`:536`). Dot3/hemispheric data are filled **only** when `ms_currentLights.parallelSpecular[0]` is non-null — i.e. a `T_parallel` light survived `selectLights` (`:423-440`, `:542-609`). With an empty filtered light list, D3D9 **explicitly uploads zeros** for dot3 RGB and hemispheric RGB (`:610-625`, `:531-533`, `:725`).

**D3D11 gates the same constants on `s_pixelDot3State.valid`**, set only when `psSlot != nullptr` after the directional cascade (`Direct3d11_LightManager.cpp:85`, `:176-196`). Producer B (`StaticShaderData::apply`) writes PS **c0–c4** only inside `if (d3.valid)` (`Direct3d11_StaticShaderData.cpp:945-957`). Producer A for VS (`composeSlot0Shadow`) fills **c40–c43** and **c60–c63** only inside the same gate (`Direct3d11_StateCache.cpp:382-415`).

There are **no** functions named `getDot3*`, `getBackColor`, or `getTangentColor`. Values come from `Light` getters invoked inline.

---

## 1. Getter / writer inventory (file:line)

### D3D9 — data sources (“getters”)

| Role | Actual call site | File:line |
|------|------------------|-----------|
| Scaled vs unscaled dispatch | `getPossiblyScaledDiffuseColor`, `getPossiblyScaledDiffuseBackColor`, `getPossiblyScaledDiffuseTangentColor`, `getPossiblyScaledSpecularColor` member pointers | `Direct3d9_LightManager.cpp:63-68`, set at `:318-338` |
| World light axis | `light->getObjectFrameK_w()` | `:547`, `:785` |
| Object-local direction (negated) | `ms_objectToWorldTransform.rotate_p2l(direction)` then `-d.{x,y,z}` | `:573-576`, `:786-789` |
| Dot3 diffuse | `(light->*getPossiblyScaledDiffuseColor)()` | `:552-556`, `:801-805` |
| Dot3 specular | `(light->*getPossiblyScaledSpecularColor)()` | `:558-562`, `:807-811` |
| Hemispheric back | `(light->*getPossiblyScaledDiffuseBackColor)()` | `_vsps_setExtendedLightData` `:739-743` |
| Hemispheric tangent | `(light->*getPossiblyScaledDiffuseTangentColor)()` | `:745-749` |
| `tangentMinusBack` delta | `tangentColor - backColor` (component-wise) | `:751-754` |
| `tangentMinusDiffuse` delta | `tangentColor - diffuseColor`; `.a = bloomEnabled` | `:756-759` |
| Specular power in direction.w | `Direct3d9_StateCache::getSpecularPower()` | `:577`, `:790` |
| Object-local camera | `ms_objectToWorldTransform.rotateTranslate_p2l(ms_cameraPosition)` | `:567-571`, `:777-781` |
| Alpha-fade / bloom `.a` packing | `Direct3d9::getAlphaFadeAndBloomSettings()` | `:579`, `:617`, `:799`, `:859` |

`Light::getScaledDiffuseBackColor()` / `getScaledDiffuseTangentColor()` are defined at `Light.h:218-227`. Default construction is `VectorArgb::solidBlack` for both (`Light.cpp:40-45`).

`ms_noDot3Light[3]` is defined (`Direct3d9_LightManager.cpp:53`) but **never referenced** anywhere else in the repo — not a fallback path.

### D3D9 — upload sites

| Target | Function | File:line |
|--------|----------|-----------|
| PS **c0–c4** (`PSCR_dot3LightDirection`…`TangentMinusBackColor`) | `applyLights_vertexShader` → `setPixelShaderConstants(PSCR_dot3LightDirection, &pixelDot3Data, 5)` | `:592-601` (lit), `:614-624` (empty slot 0) |
| PS fast-path direction-only | `applyLights_vertexShader_dot3` | `:823-830`, `:844` |
| VS **c16–c43** (`VSCR_lightData`, 28 float4) incl. dot3 @ **c40–c43** | `setVertexShaderConstants(VSCR_lightData, &lightData, 28)` | `:723` |
| VS **c60–c63** (`VCSR_extendedLightData`) | `setVertexShaderConstants(VCSR_extendedLightData, &extendedLightData, …)` | `:725` |
| Hemispheric fill helper | `_vsps_setExtendedLightData` | `:732-760` |
| Precalc ambient floor toggle | `setFullAmbientOn(m_fullAmbient)` where `m_fullAmbient = shader.containsPrecalculatedVertexLighting()` | `Direct3d9_StaticShaderData.cpp:776`, `:955` |

Register map: `VSCR_lightData = 16` (`Direct3d9_VertexShaderConstantRegisters.h:28`); dot3 is last 4 float4 of the 28-float4 `LightData` struct (`Direct3d9_LightManager.h:128-136`) → **c40–c43**. `VCSR_extendedLightData = 60` (`Direct3d9_VertexShaderConstantRegisters.h:45`). PS dot3 enum starts at 0 (`Direct3d9_PixelShaderConstantRegisters.h:23-27`).

### D3D11 — equivalent paths

| Role | Site | File:line |
|------|------|-----------|
| Snapshot capture (world-space) | `psSlot->getObjectFrameK_w()`, `getScaledDiffuseColor/Specular/Back/Tangent` | `Direct3d11_LightManager.cpp:178-195` |
| `valid` flag | `s_pixelDot3State.valid = false` on entry; `= true` only inside `if (psSlot)` | `:85`, `:176-196` |
| PS **c0–c4** (Producer B, object-local at draw) | `if (d3.valid) { … memcpy staging @ PSCR_dot3* }` | `Direct3d11_StaticShaderData.cpp:945-957` |
| VS **c16** ambient | `s_slot0Shadow.lightData[0] = d3.ambient` (unconditional) | `Direct3d11_StateCache.cpp:380` |
| VS **c17–c19**, **c40–c43**, **c60–c63** | `if (d3.valid) { … }` | `Direct3d11_StateCache.cpp:382-415` |
| VS **c20–c23** parallel fill/bounce | unconditional loop over `d3.parallelDirectionWorld[]` | `:425-430` |
| Hemispheric deltas | same formulas as D3D9 `_vsps_setExtendedLightData` | `Direct3d11_LightManager.cpp:190-193` |

**D3D11 has no `setFullAmbientOn` equivalent** — grep across `Direct3d11/` returns zero matches.

---

## 2. Empty-list + precalc + `setFullAmbientOn(true)` in D3D9

### What “empty list” means in engine code

Per draw, `ShaderPrimitiveSorter::Phase::draw` calls `setLights(i->lightBitSet)` (`ShaderPrimitiveSorter.cpp:718`), which builds `ms_activeLightList` from enabled bits (`:1130-1144`) and passes it to `Graphics::setLights`. Precalc primitives are queued with `ms_lightsAffectingShadersWithPrecalculatedVertexLighting` (`:1198-1199`). Lights default to affecting both precalc and non-precalc shaders (`Light.cpp:61-62`).

An “empty” list means **no lights in that filtered `ms_activeLightList`**, so after `selectLights` all slots including `parallelSpecular[0]` remain `NULL` (`Direct3d9_LightManager.cpp:377-378`, `:407-476`).

### Trace: does full-ambient or a default sun populate dot3?

**No.**

1. `setFullAmbientOn(true)` → `ms_fullAmbient = (1,1,1,0)` (`Direct3d9_LightManager.h:203-208`).
2. `selectLights` → `ms_currentLights.ambient = ms_fullAmbient` (`Direct3d9_LightManager.cpp:404`). No code assigns a default `T_parallel` when the list is empty.
3. `applyLights_vertexShader`:
   - `Zero(lightData)` and `Zero(extendedLightData)` (`:531-533`) → VS dot3 @ c40–c43 and ext @ c60–c63 are **all zero**.
   - `parallelSpecular[0]` is null → `i == 0` else branch (`:610-625`):
     - `Zero(pixelDot3Data)` (`:615`)
     - Only `.a` channels patched from alpha-fade/bloom/time; **`.xyz` and `.rgb` stay zero**
     - Uploaded to PS c0–c4 (`:624`)

**`setFullAmbientOn` never touches dot3 direction, diffuse/specular RGB, back, tangent, or deltas.** The sun getter (`getObjectFrameK_w`) runs only inside `if (light)` at `:543-609`.

### D3D9 literal values — empty-list precalc draw

| Constant | Register | Value (empty list) | Evidence |
|----------|----------|-------------------|----------|
| `dot3.localDirection` (PS c0 / VS c41) | PS c0, VS c41 | `(0, 0, 0, 0)` — **no** `getSpecularPower()` write in empty branch | `:615`, `:531` |
| `dot3.diffuseColor` (PS c1 / VS c42) | PS c1, VS c42 | `rgb = (0,0,0)`; PS `.a = alphaFade.r` | `:619`, `:615` |
| `dot3.specularColor` (PS c2 / VS c43) | PS c2, VS c43 | `rgb = (0,0,0)`; PS `.a = alphaFade.a` | `:620` |
| `tangentMinusDiffuseColor` (PS c3 / VS c63) | PS c3, VS c63 | `rgb = (0,0,0)`; PS `.a = bloom.g` | `:621` |
| `tangentMinusBackColor` (PS c4 / VS c62) | PS c4, VS c62 | `rgb = (0,0,0)`; PS `.a = currentTime` | `:622` |
| `backColor` (VS c60) | VS c60 | `(0,0,0,0)` | `Zero(extendedLightData)` `:533` |
| `tangentColor` (VS c61) | VS c61 | `(0,0,0,0)` | same |
| `lightData.ambient` (VS c16) | VS c16 | `(1,1,1,0)` when precalc + `setFullAmbientOn(true)` | `:404`, `:536`, `StaticShaderData.cpp:955` |

**Correction vs prior framing:** D3D9 does **not** use full-ambient or a built-in default light to make dot3/hemispheric nonzero on an empty list. Both APIs produce **zero** dot3/hemispheric RGB in that scenario. Your RenderDoc axiom (v1 = 0 in both frames; only PS packedRegister1/3/4 flip) is consistent with this — the variable is the **directional dot3 pack**, not c16.

### D3D9 stale-constant edge case (not empty-list first upload)

If `ms_currentLights` is unchanged and `parallelSpecular[0]` is null, `applyLights_vertexShader_dot3` does **nothing** unless `ms_alphaFadeOpacityDirty` (`:849-893`). That can leave **previous** GPU constants. On a **lights-changed** transition to empty, the full `applyLights_vertexShader` path **does** zero-upload (`:610-625`).

